Crusaders are heavy melee fighters who synthesize Knight formation discipline with Swordsman individual blade mastery.
The title originates as a Solar Court campaign-honor for wardens who served successive engagements without rotation.
The modern tradition formed during the Ash-and-Iron Decades when Knight and Swordsman training merged in shared reserve depots.
Core doctrine: chain the Knight's body-strike mechanics into the Swordsman's escalating momentum for force exceeding either path alone.
Combat role is sustained offensive melee pressure combining coordinated strikes with building intensity.
Key ability: Anti Magic Shell, a defensive technique developed against magical disruption.
This is a remort class requiring training in both Knight and Swordsman traditions.
The Crusader Corps is organized as a formal corps with shared doctrine and institutional identity.
The tradition represents the resolution of the rivalry between formation doctrine and individual excellence.
